      <p>The main feature we had difficulty finalizing was the upload feature. At first, we decided that we wanted
        to implement an user profile feature. This way, we could keep track of uploads and users could favorite certain
        locations. However, we found later through testing that user profiles were unnecessary. Using FluidUI allowed us to
        conduct user testing without constructing the actual application. However, we also conducted various
        user testing on our live version. This way, we knew which areas were problems and if bugs existed in our code.
        During user testing, we utilized certain criteria to evaluate usability.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Frequency of use for specific features</li>
        <li>Time elapsed to complete a certain use case</li>
        <li>Any user confusion</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Uploading became an issue for many users during testing. During our first iteration, we implemented uploading
        in the profile section. Many of our users spent too much time trying to figure out where the upload function was
        located. So, we decided to move upload to our main page. Moving our upload function helped our application flow
        better. We also conducted A/B testing to determine the usability of a user profile page. We found that many users
        chose to ignore the profile page and opted to find locations as a "guest." The low usage of our profile feature
        prompted us to remove the feature altogether.
      </p>
